    <description>Doomed Battalions is the Allied Minor extension to the Advanced Squad Leader game system.[...]&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Doomed Battalions contains:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    3 8&amp;quot; x 22&amp;quot; geomorphic mapboards (9, 44, and 45) (1st-2nd edition) / 5 8&amp;quot; x 22&amp;quot; geomorphic mapboards (9, 11, 33, 44, and 45) (3rd edition)&amp;#10;    3 countersheets (2nd edition) / 4 countersheets (3rd edition)&amp;#10;    7 ASL scenarios (1st-2nd edition) / 24 ASL scenarios (3rd edition)&amp;#10;    Chapter H notes for the Allied Minors&amp;#10;    Overlays OW1, RR1-RR14, X19-X24&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;3rd edition note: this edition contains both Doomed Battalions (1st-2nd edition) and The Last Hurrah so the entire Allied Minor OB - infantry, support weapons, guns, and vehicles - is available in one module. &amp;#10;Includes an additional countersheet and mapboards 11 &amp;amp; 33.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Doomed Battalions is not a complete game, Beyond Valor , the ASL Rulebook, and several other Advanced Squad Leader ASL boards are required for play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Scenario List:&amp;#10;[3rd edition only, originally published in The Last Hurrah:]&amp;#10;ASL 43     Into the Fray            &amp;#10;ASL 44     The Gauntlet              &amp;#10;ASL 45     Revenge at Kastelli        &amp;#10;ASL 46     Birds of Prey              &amp;#10;ASL 47     Rude Awakening             &amp;#10;ASL 48     Toujours L'Audace          &amp;#10;ASL 49     Piercing the Peel          &amp;#10;ASL 50     Age Old Foes&amp;#10;&amp;#10;[All editions:]&amp;#10;ASL 83     An Uncommon Occurrence     &amp;#10;ASL 84     Round One                  &amp;#10;ASL 85     No Way Out                &amp;#10;ASL 86     Fighting Back             &amp;#10;ASL 87     Good Night, Sweet Prince   &amp;#10;ASL 89     Rescue Attempt            &amp;#10;ASL 90     Pride and Joy&amp;#10;&amp;#10;[3rd edition only, originally from various issues of the ASL Annual, The General, ASL